\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That's right - that was his father. Yes. That was his father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she have any other jobs until she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Only cleaning in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
nights in - what was the shop now in Bowls Street - Cripps. It was a great big shop. She used to go and do the showrooms at night. An
d walk - walk home from the Pierhead and then go to Miss Rathbone's the next day. I can remember Miss Rathbone coming for her and - Miss Eleanor we used to call her - she - she - I heard her say to mother once - oh try and come Mrs Walker. Mother had a ve
ry bad ulcer on her leg and she couldn't go for a couple of days and - said, do try and come Mrs Walker, we don't get near the work that you give us. I can remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your mother must have been an old timer mustn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She was, yes. She made us work you know. Yes. We all had to have a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who looked after the children while your mother was at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well the eldest one looked after the younger ones and that's how we went on. I was the housekeeper for years. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How many rooms were there in the biggest house you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Three bedrooms. Yes. Well, two and a box}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any reception rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh, parlour, kitchen and back kitchen. No bathroom of course. We used to light the boiler for the bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No other relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your washing was done at home - at least, it was sent to the wash house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I used - when I was fourteen I had to go to the wash house - with ours, with ours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Those wash houses were wonderful things weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh she used to - mother'd say, now you - you do this and she'd wrap it i
n a bundle - now that goes in cold water first and then when you scrub them touch them up with a brush, you put them in the boiler and I got the routine that - give it to you know just as she gave it to me. We were trained in those days. We were capable o
f looking after any man we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 . Nowadays they're not. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. She was no good with a needle. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were the clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well some of them were new, some she had given to her of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did you buy them when you bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we used to get a check and go to Stalers or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How many people know what a check's like - you and I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Well - a - a clothing voucher. So much a week. Like a mail order. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 But you had to have a good reputation before you'd get a check?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I say - and a good clean rent book.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They examined your rent book before you got the check?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How about the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well sometimes we got them through the school and we had a card and paid sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That's unusual - I've never heard of that - what was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. You could go down to the education and - get shoes and you - got them at half price and you paid what you could every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did you get the shoes from - from the education or from a shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh they were sent up to your school and you signed for them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And you paid weekly for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Anybody repair them - having no father he couldn't sole them for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No, well we went to the boot repairers then. You only paid coppers then to get your boots mended. They lasted for - for ages. Not like now - they're only brown paper. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You don't know much about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You don't know if he did any repairing or cooking or cleaning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No. No he didn't. Sometimes if he was - when he was on the docks mother said if he was out of work he'd mend them but if he was working he wouldn't. He said, another man had to hav
e a living. Although they were good parents you know as regards - their teaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any jobs you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, I took milk out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 At home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh, you mean in the house? Oh yes, I had to help with the - ironing after she'd washed and clean the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you continue doing this after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your brothers and sisters have regular jobs too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well the boys went to sea. Yes, after they left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 All the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How about the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they went into service. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they have any jobs at home before they left school - say, somebody do the washing somebody do the floors - did you all have jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - we - we - like as we left school - the one that was older, if she went into service well her - all her work'd fall on me. It went rotation way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 But you all had jobs laid out for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the older children help the younger with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Such as dressing and eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well, no, we were pretty well - the boys didn't have to do it, the girls did. While they were at home, but when they went the eldest one saw to the younger ones you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the younger children help the older ones in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. We had to. After we come from Band of Hope or - whenever it was we had - a drink of cocoa and off to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, we just - stripped off and got washed in turn and up to bed - up the dancers she used to say, up the dancers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh - I'd be about - I can't remember the proper age, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Being the youngest you wouldn't remember anybody else would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well next to youngest I was you see. I used to see to A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 y and take her to bed so I suppose if I had her and done I'd - I'd - do myself wouldn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you share the bedroom or bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we had to share bedrooms - too many of us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What were the sleeping arrangements of the whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - you mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The boys in one room, the girls in another and your mother and father in the third room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we slept to the same room as mother. The boys slept in their own you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Of course, your dad was dead then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No father you see. And when the boys were all at home we didn't have a par
lour for sitting in - we had a bed down there because - the oldest boys you know and then of course you know we made it up a parlour after a few of them left - gone to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your husband died when you were very young didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, twenty-six I was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And your father died - your mother was a widow for many, many years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. She was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh, the back kitchen. Light the boiler and a big bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How often did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we use
d to have two a week, if we - if we - only had one at home if we'd gone to the baths but I couldn't swim - I - I was too nervous to swim so I had - didn't go to the baths. The boys went to the baths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you had to have two did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, I had to have two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we had them every Saturday night. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well in very poor days of a morning we used to get up and go to the school and get cocoa and - and jam or treacle bread. Queensland Street.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the school give you that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes, we went there - yes, had a voucher for breakfast. And - and I - they used to call me the lady because the bread was cut too thick and I wouldn't eat it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And that's what you got - just cocoa and....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Piece of treacle bread or jam bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What about - say a weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we had it coming - we could go then and buy a leg of lamb for one and nine. And a piece of brisket for sixpence. And it just depended ho
w much money mother had whether we had brisket and roast potatoes or hot pot and we used to make the hot pot in a big pan mug in the oven you know. Oh it smelt beautiful just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother have a range to cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. We had a - kitchen oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Not a gas range - just a range?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When you had your breakfast at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you all present during that meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, there'd be - a lot of them at that time was away from home, you know. They'd all - dispersed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And some of them would have to go out early if they were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes. Well you see two of the boys went to - sea one after the other and then the eldest boy, Joseph, he went on the Blackpool pleasure boats, so he wasn't at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The Blackpool pleasure boats - from Liverpool to Blackpool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, they were boats from Blackpool to somewhere else weren't they, you know. He worked away though he wasn't very long there before he }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you usually have for your breakfast when you had it at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we only had fried bread or - something like that those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I often wonder how on earth we survived don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I do. Yes, but - you know, I don't know, I think the food was better - the bread. My mother used 
to bake bread and she'd leave it and we'd take it to the bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
house. We didn't have any of this manufactured stuff like we've got now. It's all - what shall I say - a food now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It's synthetic isn't it - artific}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 al?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I was just going to say - there's no nut}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 ri}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
ent in it you know. No. I said to the doctor last week that I - I said when I get up of a morning and get dressed I'm that weak I want to get back into bed again. And he gave - he said, you're short of vitamins C's. He says, you don't bother t
o cook. I said, don't bother to cook, I said, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What were your meals on Sunday - did you have anything different on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh aye, we had a few currant cakes at tea time or an apple pie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, sometimes we had a bi
t of bacon but in those days mostly it was salt fish. And - mother wouldn't have the ordinary fish - it had to be ling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was the white stuff wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. And - of course that was a bit dearer so - we didn't always have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That used to be soaked all night didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. And skinned. You had to skin it - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You put a little bit of margarine on it didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We did. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
 the margarine was as good as butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember the Maypole stuff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, slappin
g with the - the two - putting all the was - putting all the water in to - to make it weigh heavy. I can see them now - taking those pats out and shake it on the paper - oh. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And sometimes you had a shoulder of mutton or shoulder of lamb?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Aye, or a leg or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother make her won bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Always. No, we had to go and have a jar of jam in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Or bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. Not those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she make any wine or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, she did sometimes. She used to make this - sulphur and treacle. We used to dodge away so as she couldn't find us to give it to us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We used to get a dollp every weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 G}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 regory powder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Then licorice powder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh. They kept us best didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they keep any hens or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, she had a couple of hens. Yes. Aye.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we had to clean them out and - the boys cleaned them out and - we used to make their food and give it to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we had it - two or three times. Perhaps more. We always had a - a hot dinner at night. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was it tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no. No, we always went to the butcher. I know it was liver and onions on the Thursday - every Thursdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever get any extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, we got rabbits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Not from poaching - you had to boy a fourpenny one or a ninepenny one didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well to tell you the truth she'd so many of us that when she gave us all food I don't ever remember her sitting down and eating with us.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You don't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. But she was terribly fond - if we wanted to give}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 her a treat I can 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No. But she was terribly fond - if we wanted to giver her a treat I can remember we'd go out and we'd bring her back a bloater. She loved a bloater. Yes, yes. Yes. Bloaters and red herrings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You don't see them now do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Bloaters were herrings were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They were herrings yes, cured.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They were very salty weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, the red herrings were but the bloaters weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And another thing we used to make - potted herrings - you don't see those now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I used to love potted herrings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. She used to do a lot of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 During a meal were you allowed to talk or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no. We didn't - we weren't allowed to - to put a book up and read either while - while we were eating - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no. No, we all had the same, it didn't run to individual dishes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we never left it, I can't remember us leaving it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it to you or did you have to
 wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no, we asked. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, if she had it we got it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you bring books or a toy to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When we asked and said grace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You did say grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, before and after. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did all the family sit at the table for a meal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. All those that were in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you always have the same place at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How was the meal served - you told me your mother served it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she serve it from a tureen or direct from the dish in which she cooked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - it was cooked - she had a little table at the window and - she had our plates there and - one of them would be up. But she'd serve the dinner you know and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 she'd say - that's F}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 lo's - that's Amy's - that's so and so, but she always started the eldest one. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - all the brothers were older than me. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You won't remember those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You wouldn't remember who fed you when you were a little kiddie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh, mother fed us all 'til we were - you know, a certain age. There was no food bought at the chemist like there was now. No. Porridge - gruel they used to take - and then they used to feed and sometimes mother said, she used
 to give us a - one or two spoonfuls of the gruel if we were hungry babies. Yes. Well it's just the same as that Farex and Groats - as they say, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, she was a wonderful - no, she was a wonderful woman, wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did your mother expect you to behave towards her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - she didn't expect - whatever we - 
we knew what was our obligation to her you see. And - yes, if we wanted to know anything we went and asked or - asked her if it would be all right to do this or do that or go here or go there. We always did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I never remember her saying that. She used to say to us, if anyone hurt you walk away from them - don
't answer back. And don't hurt them. Yes. Go away - don't stand and - quarrel with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be? Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life? What did you think your mother wanted you to be when you grew up - what kind of person?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well she wanted us to be good living - at first, you know, and look after our home and - and - children. But - she never said she expected us to be - great things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did your mother think you should consider most important in life? Truthfulness - honesty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes. Well she - always wanted us to be good to each other you know and - and if we could do a good turn for anybody else - she used to say, you not - never 
lose by it. She always said that. Yes. It comes - even if that person, she said, doesn't appreciate it at the time you will be paid back. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did she think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh that was terrible. Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes. If you said damn or blast she'd say, now there's no need for that. Must you say it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Not when we were children, no, we were - we were sent away to play, now go and play, we weren't allowed to hear anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If you did something your mother didn't like what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we got a good reprimand and we perhaps got a little crack with something. On the knuckles or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember any particular occasion when you were punished for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We
ll yes, I was once. When I was going out with me husband you know - courting and - I came back a bit late and she was behind the door. I needn't tell you what happened. She wasn't having me a little stop-out. That's what she said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you feel about that - were you highly indignant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well now I laugh but then I thought she was terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Would you received the ideas you had about how to behave from your mother - you must have done mustn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You had no father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You must have got them from your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Any guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Can you remember anything you did with your mother together on Christmas Day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No. We all had our - whatever it was you know - our meals and that but - we didn't have any sing-songs and - like they have now and going to the pubs and things like that. We didn't have any of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. We used to - Christmas Day at night time we used to all sit round the fire singing Wesley hymns. Yes. That was the only thing we had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you make music together - you didn't have a piano did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We had a gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 phone. Yes. Yes. Phonograph. One of those with the round things - yes, Edison - Edison Bell is it. I've got a gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 ophone now in the bedroom}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. She'd too much hard work to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any books in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Only the books that we got from Sunday school and places like that you know. She wouldn't let us read the others. No, nor a newspaper.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She wouldn't have any newspapers in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She wouldn't let us read them. No. Not until we got - you know, to be age that we left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember your mother reading at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she ever read aloud to you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In our family? You mean, before mother died or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Up 'til 1918. Your mother reared all her children didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was unusual in itself wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember any funerals in the street at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, I remember an old woman dying once and they asked em to go to St Bernard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 s, you know St Bernard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 s church, it's called our Lady of Lourdes now in Kingley Road and - ask for - a priest for some candles, blessed candles. And - I went down, it was a priest called Father Ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5969602\charrsid4015401 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
ris, he was a convert priest. And they gave me four candles and I run back and - when I went back the woman was in the room with this old lady that had died. Oh and I thought it was a terrible - sight. She was an Irish 
woman and she was about ninety - gaunt. A real face that would frighten you you know, not a bit -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Not peaceful?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. And - I never wanted to see a corpse after that. No. But - that's the only funeral I know and the priest came up shortly afterwar
ds and gave me a penny. Cos I - I think he came to see if I really had taken the candles you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother take you visiting neighbours, friends or relatives?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, sometimes we'd shop but - mother was so busy occupied that we had to do the shopping ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In other words the shopping was just going messages wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. There were no fridges - we brought from day to day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You always went with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember any other outings with your mother - did you go anywhere on a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, we had to go to Sefton Park ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember the rack on Sefton Park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 There's one in the - over in - what do you call it - New 
Brighton - the rack and - the Ham and egg parade. We used to go over to New Brighton for tuppence ha'penny return. A penny on the tram all the way to the Pier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4854737\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 head. I had to pay two shillings now if I want to go to town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Any member of the family ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you tell me how you spent Saturday in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Well Saturdays - it was the normal thing - cleaning - cleaning and messages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you do on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well we got up on a Sunday morning as you know and - we had our breakfast, went to church, we came back and we'd have a bit of dinner. And then we'd go to Sunday school. We wouldn't miss that because we used to get our little text tickets you know. And - 
then we came back and had tea. Well we went to church again in the evening for the - in the summer but she wouldn't let us out in the winger in the dark. We wouldn't go. Not the younger ones. The older ones could go but we couldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have different clothes on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, we had - the same clothes washed on a Saturday you know and ironed and done up. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you play any games on Sunday or did your mother think it was wrong to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Ooh, we darent touch anything on a Sunday. One day had to be different to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother go to any church at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, she used to go to - well she went for years to St Nathaniel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4854737\charrsid4015401 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That's church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How often did she go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well she used to go - if she could, she used to go Monday nights and - I think there was something on a Wednesday or a Thursday, I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you go to that church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You went to the Mission didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We went to the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You told me you went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, there were, yes. But they were only to little parks and things you know. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You used to go in a wagonette didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Or on the tr
am. Tommy Sales used to - you know, the man that lived up at Tunnel Road, the book repairer. Yes. Yes. Well he used to give a day outing once a year you know, but he - it always fell on a day when - it was a workday, like I had to - and I couldn't go. But
 I think really she used to keep us away because she saw the children hanging over the top of the trams and - you know - she was frightened. Oh they used to go frantic didn't they, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any other social activities organised by the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Only their parties what they'd have in the hall you know. The church missions and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. I used to sing on a Sunday - go out - picked out to sing a hymn or - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 There wouldn't be a choir in that mission would there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4854737\charrsid4015401 Did your chapel run a tem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 perance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh all the top - head people went to the - churches where there was choirs. Poor people went to these little halls and - and missions. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your chapel run a temperance club - a Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you a member of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, I was in the band of Hope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you do at the Band of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we used to go and sing and - and - have games sometimes and - sometimes they'd give us a
 - a paper with poetry on that we had to learn and if we said it the next week without a - a mistake we got a prize and - oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I suppose you made your own concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh yes. We used to have concerts in the back yard sometime - and had to clear all up before your mother came home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, always - before and after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we used to kneel by mother before we went to bed you know, and just say a little prayer you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your mother's political attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you know what her attitude was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Political attitude - she was a Tory all her life. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Why do you think she held these views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - because me father was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember her voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well now let me see - when was Jack Hyes in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Jack Hayes was 1922.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh well, she was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She wouldn't have a vote would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
In some places men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employer - you don't know about your father do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh, only that he was Tory. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Being a public house manager it was automatic wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I couldn't imagine anybody being anything but a Tory if he was a public house manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It wouldn't be safe would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was your mother a member of the Conservative party do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she take part in any political activity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When your mother was not doing her work how did she spend her time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She never had any spare time - that was the trouble.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she have any interests outside the home at all - you said she went to church now and again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself - to a whist drive or anything?
