Nobody paid - if you were - if your mother was a widow and - you were a certain age you got them free. It was only piece of treacle bread and a cup of cocoa you know. It was a treat if we got jam. Well we were healthy - look at the age
. No, to think that we come through it all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Sometimes we had lard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Fried bread, yes, fried was the - in the winter fried bread. It was a warm breakfast. Yes. We - we've had porridge for our dinner you know or a rice pudding - no meat and potatoes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Or a sc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
ambled egg amongst three of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Do you remember the - milk floats that used to call - on a Sunday morning mother used to have the jug ready and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
pence I think it was and we had to rush out for}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401  the skimmed milk to make the r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ice pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And it was always blue wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Like starch water. Oh dear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It was threeha'pence a quart I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Well we had to have a big rice pudding and a great big round pan mug on a tin dish because - oh it was funny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We're better off now than we were ; then aren't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we are in some things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The only thing our parents had to look f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 rward to was the workhouse wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - oh well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 My mother and father were frightened to death of the workhouse.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
My mother wasn't, neither was I. When - the first operation I had, I had in Smithdown Road, it was a workhouse hospital and I couldn't have had - I had the best specialist out of Rodney Street - Leyland Robinson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was in the hospital part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 But old people were separated from one another weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they could see each other in the grounds but they didn't sleep together. It was a - a semi divorce.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We were talking about class weren't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What class or group would you say you belonged to yourself or your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we were only working - you know. Hard working British people. That's what we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What sort of people belonged to the same class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh simi
lar. I - when I go to this class this welfare class there'd two people that I went to school with. Their living in their house - they worked - all hours to save you know and get money. But bought a house. Yes. They live over on Tarbuck Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What sort of people belonged to the other groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
You mean the - the moneyed people. Well they all worked you know, I can't see that - people seem to think the people I mixed with - and mother mixed with - she used to do a - a little job now and again for Ban
ner Gwyreth is it, the fruit merchants. Well they lived off Lodge Lane in - is it Sefton Grove - one of those -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That's getting up to rather the rich part isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. Well - they were nice people. They were very nice. The mistress used to
 come in the kitchen and speak to you quite friendly you know. Yes. I think that was the - highest I went to until - of course this last war when the - the war - the Lord Mayorps War Fund you know, I used to run dances in Georges Hall. And I think the las
t I gave - Denton was the Lord Mayor - I gave thirty-eight pound to that, yes. I got nice letters here you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you meet the rich people there at St Georges Hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I met Denton and - and all, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently to people of another sort?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh show respect but not curtsey. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who were you taught to show respect to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well anybody o
lder - anybody sick, we had to help them you know, go messages and do. And - any older children, we had to - sort of - do what they told us you know, if they were older than us we had to - you know, look up to them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was there anyone you called Sir or Master or Madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. Funny I never did. No, not - when I worked in the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market in town you know I used to just say good morning and - and - that, we - we were told not to call any their names out in public you know. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When were you at the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Now let me see - oh I was only a very young woman then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no - after. After, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well mother you know, I don't remember father. No. Yes, I think my mother was treated very nicely. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In the area where you were living who was considered the most important person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Now let's see. I think the minister. Yes. I think the minister when he visited us
 you know. We'd all run in and we'd sit there and have a talk. Mother used to hold little prayer meetings you know. The - what do they call those ladies - at churches - oh dear - Deaconess. Yes they Deaconess used to come and mother used to tidy all round
 - she'd be at work but - almost - almost all of the time but - if she wasn't there the Deaconess would come in and I'd know exactly what to do and she'd hold this little meeting about seven or eight people - church meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you came into contact with the minister quite often then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember why he was considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. We never thought about it you know, didn't think we were important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Why did you think he was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh why we thought he was. Well because he used to teach us the right from wrong. Mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever come into contact with shopkeepers in the area where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, we used to go to Poulters in Lodge Lane - do you know Poulters? And Cauley - Gorley Brothers in Dobb Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who do you think they mixed up with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well they - the shopkeepers - well, they didn't - mix with us because they didn't live in our neighbourhood, you see. But - in the shop - they always had a joke and was always pleasant. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who did the clergyman mixed up with - did he mix up with the people, live amongst them or did he live in another area?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - Musgrave Brown he - he lived in another area. But he - he mixed with us and our parents when it was Harvest Festival
 and we were training for that, you know, for singing and - all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Can you tell me anything about the teachers - who did the teachers mix up with - did they live in the area or did they have a special group who they mixed up with or did they mix up with the ministers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well a couple of them lived in the area but - the headmistress and the headmaster of the school I think they lived away - in another district. In those days - I think - it was so that they wouldn't favour children -
 they were brought from another neighbourhood, the heas. But a couple of the lower - teachers that - that teach - taught the lower classes, they lived - one lived in Solway Street - Miss - Miss Phelps and Miss Coope}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  lived in Aspen Grove, Lodge Lane. And another one lived in Tiber Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Did you ever come into contact with employers at that time when you were a little girl? Did the employers mix with the workers, the clergy, the farmers or teachers? You wouldn't come into contact with employers would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I didn't because - you mean I was working or when I was going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When you were going to school or when you were first working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well only - when - as I tell you mother used to do Frisby Dyke's washing and we'd go down there the - manager Mr Freeman at F}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
isby Dykes. Sometimes he'd be there you know in the - staff place and - they used to have a staff hall where they had their meals you see, and we used to have to go in that entrance. Well they were all nice, all the girls, yes. And the - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What sort of people would you say went to church and what sort of people went to chapel? The difference between church and chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, there is. Well - I think the poorer people went to the chapels and the mission halls and - 
as I say in - in schooldays you did go to church for to train for the singing you see. But - we knew our church and the - when we began to get older we automatically went into the church you see. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where you lived did all the people in the wor
king class have the same standard of living or would you say there was different types of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well I think - no, there weren't different types of living but - where there was a father they got more - they had more you see. But - where there was n
o father you were sort of pinned down to a limit with clothes and food and things, but where there was a father and if he was in regular work, which there was very few those days, the painters - I was only thinking this morning, we had friends that - that
 went to school with me and they - they were out of work half the year - no work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Could you describe the standard of living of a very poor person like yourself? Well - people who had no parents? You were telling me about the unemployed painters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401  - that 
would go for the docker}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 s to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Painters. Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh they'd go down you know, the dockers, sometimes they'd sign on three and four times a day and - to stand and picked out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Like cattle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. But you see at that time when that all - all that unemployment was we had a big influx }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1908821\charrsid4015401 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
oom - Ireland didn't we because they were having a bad time. And they all went for the docks and the coal heaving. Yes. I know my - husband's uncle used to bring all the coal heavers over from 
Ireland. Yes. He lived - in Athel - Sylevesters Street. Yes. Yes. And he used to bring them all over - he was secretary for the coal heavers union for thirty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And there were lodging houses there weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He - he used to put a lot of the coal heavers up, yes. Yes, he turned his - it over to Jimmy Sexton.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He ended up Sir James Sexton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes, and the other poor old - man you know he - he used to go round of a - coal heaver died and pay them the five
 pound union money out of his own pocket and wait 'til it - he got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you tell me if one group felt itself better than another group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, if - you went to school and you weren't in ex seven that was the highest you could go - you were
 very much looked down and - if you went to a - a place of work like I did at first, getting trained for domestic and that sort of thing and the others went in a shop, oh they thought they were crowing well over you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 An employed man - one that worked 
on the trams or on the railway - would you think he was superior or would they think he was superior to a man who worked on the docks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I don't think so. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, they were. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen or tradesmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well there was a distinction but not a snobby one. You know. Because I remember a - a - man that did this ornamental plastering and he worked at the Em
pire when it first opened, you know, when it was rebuilt and he had a lot of work there. Well now that man earned what we call then a tremendous wage and we lived next door to them but - he never forgot that we had no father and every Saturday, you know, 
if it was only tuppence we got it each, the same as his own children. 'Course we could go with a farthing then and buy sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He was an exception wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. We could go with a farthing and buy sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your see herself as belonging to a social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you say why she belonged to this - because of where she lived or because of her job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - I think it was both really mixed in, you know, because - the people were all working people as you know and t
hey all did similar to what she was doing - the women and - they got in - sort of together. If - as I told you - if my mother was ill and couldn't go to her job she would go to one of these women and ask her to take her place rather than the people that s
he worked for be let down. And that's how they worked together you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was it possible at that time to move from one group to a higher group.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well if you were doing better - if you were progressing you know and - got -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you know anybody who ever did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You mean - mix in another group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Personally I can't remember it but you might have some experience of a person who lives in your group and then later on in life became rather better off?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, there was a few like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you think they got better jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - I think it was they were attentive to their work and they were capable of doing the job that was offered to them and then - employer you know - would help them a lot too then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember anybody being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh yes. Yes. I - I met a - a lot of nice people for instance I met Margaret Bevan you know. Oh yes, she was lovely. And - and her brother was good. Well, in the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market they were all nice. They were all gentlemen. There was - Williams, Mr Williams}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 n in the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
market, there was the Cornelius's - they were wonderful people, yes. And there was the Holt's the shipping people used to come in the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market for lunch. And - it was underneath the - you see, they used to do business with the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
market - it wasn't the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market public house, it was the corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 
-}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market building, it was bombed in the war you know, yes. And there was the Sykes. Oh the Sykes were marvellous.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Can you tell me why you thought they were nice - why you thought they were ladies and gentlemen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - I'll start with Mr Sykes first. He visited me when I was going into - for this hospital in Smithdown Road. And he asked me who was doing the operation and 
I told him Leyland Robinson. He said, well mention to him that - he's to do his best - that I said he's to do his best. So I said, oh thank you, I will. So - he wrote me a letter and he asked me while I - he found out that I was getting my wages while I w
asn't working you see, while I was in hospital and of course the boss told him no, in those days you didn't. And - he said - he wrote me this letter asking me - if - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 
he could help me with my commit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ments each week. Yes. So I didn't answer because - mother ha
d brought us up that we must not take anything off a man - us girls, we must not take anything off a man at all because it - we would be under a compliment. So - I didn't answer and then he wrote again and he sent it by hand with the boy that used to wait
 
on him and - I read it and I said to Jackie, well are you seeing to Mr Sykes - are you attending to him. He said, yes. I said, well tell him I will answer his letter. Because he'd said in this letter, while you are most reluctant - to - answer I do person
a
lly want to help. So I wrote and those days my rent was ten shillings a week and - I had the two girls at home and I wrote and told him what I had and I said I didn't - have any commitments as debts because I was always afraid - of not being able to pay t
h
em. Well - he didn't send an answer to me - he asked for a - my mother's address. I said my mother was looking after the children so I didn't have to pay and he - I sent him my mother's address and he sent my mother twenty-five shillings every week while 
I was in that hospital. And when I came out he sent me away for a month's holiday. With the children. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. The bobby. The cop or the bobby we used to call him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh well he - we used to think he was terribly stern and we were frightened of him - we were terrified of him but - sometimes he'd crack a joke when he was passing us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When you were naughty did your mother say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How do you think the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well if they were rough he - he treated them rough. But normally he'd shut his eyes to a lot. He wasn't such a bad chap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was your home rented?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Rented.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Before 1918 when you were with your mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - someone nice and some were a bit stern you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember feeling that your mother had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you think about that at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - we did everything if we thought she was having a tough time. I'll tell you this, I've gone along Lodge Lane and I've kn
ocked at doors and done steps and only got threepence or fourpence. And they'd call you in, those people, and get you to do a filthy dirty kitchen floor and give you an extra penny or something and we'd gone home with one and six and mother's been thrille
d to bits. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What difference did it make to the family when your mother was ill - was she ever ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - not for a long period, you know, just perhaps as couple of days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember what it was like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well she'd get up - she never stayed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 in bed. But - she'd sit in a chair you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever get any help from the guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, a shilling a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 week off - for each child. She used to get four shillings a week. For us four girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she have any for herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They were all right. They weren't bad as far as I can remember them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you feel about having to go to the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh it was terrible if you had to go to parish. It was terrible, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They used to get a voucher didn't they instead of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 For food. Yes. Yes. And the churches used to give a voucher for food. Yes, mother used to get one from the church. At Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 For a shilling or two shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And you were not allowed to buy butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You were only allowed to buy margarine.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Or jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You weren't allowed to buy jam, only syrup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. But if the shops knew you they did. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was there anybody in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly and was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, if a woman didn't live a good life - if she was - you know - carrying on with men or anything like that, 
or a woman that drank and neglected her children, oh they did - oh they - thought that was terrible - they had no time for anyone like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they make rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they show any action against the person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No - well they di
dn't mix with her but they didn't slight the children - mother used to always say the - the children can't help what their parents do you see. So we hadn't - we weren't told not to play with them. We - we just went on normal with the children. But - the m
other's all sort of boycotted the mother if she wasn't - if she wasn't - as she should be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I suppose I'd go when the age limit was right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When you first started that would be about five wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When you first started school what were the hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
We went at nine in the morning 'til twelve. And then - we went back again I think it was we got an hour for dinner and then we came home at quarter to four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What kind of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 A church school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Which one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 St C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 lements, Dove Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you get to school - was it far for you to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no, just went over the road, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How long did it take you to walk there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh only about three or four minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well my youngest sister went and that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I suppose your mother took you the first day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, she couldn't take us - she was - she was off at work before we left for school.
 We had our orders what was for dinner and everything, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You did come home for your dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, we came home what it was you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She left it for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She must have had a tough time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, she did, yes. And s
he never grumbled. She never grumbled. Oh I've seen her walking home at night from town, from Frisby Dykes, then going to work the next morning. But she trained us you see - she had it all - she was methodical. We had to clean our shoes and everything bef
o
re we went to bed at night, that - they had to be ready you see and that automatically went to someone as they got higher and when they left and got - went to work the next one had to come and take that job and then - we all had our work, I had to do the 
fireside and the kitchen and the youngest sister had to do something else, you know. The boys did the windows. Oh she had it all arranged for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 There were no school meals then were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, I think you could get soup - and something. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Something like the breakfast you were telling me about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes. But we never went. They used to be a - a little cook shop in Dove Street and there were two maiden ladies, they used to make soup, roast potatoes and things like that so - more or less w
e always had soup because we had our dinner when mother come home at night. So we used to go with this old jug and get a quart of soup or a pint of soup, whatever we could afford. And we had to use up the old bread and put that in you see and - that was o
ur dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you go to this school all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, same school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I think we all did didn't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You went right through and when they had nothing more to teach you they shoved you in ex seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you think about school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I liked it. Yes, I liked school those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They were very nice, we used to go to them if we needed any help you know or - we thought it was heaven if they came - they - 
they used to play with us at school time you know. Oh yes, if we were playing rounders or skipping rope or - a ball game they used to have you know, they'd come and join in with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life - such as manner, tidiness, punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes, oh yes. Yes. They used to line us up to look at our nails and - yes, and domestic - day when it was domestic science - your hair had to be fastened back and you had to be all nice and clean, your apron clean - 
oh, it was very strict and you'd so much cleaning to do after you'd you're your cooking. They showed you how to clean up. There's no training like that now you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh you got - caned with a pointer stick, you know, just one slap or two slaps what - ever you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Is that how they did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 For what offences did you get that - would it be impudence or carelessness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well if you were late more than - t
hree times in a week at school you'd have to stand - take your turn. She'd ask you why you were late you see because there was so many of the children would have a little game on the way to school and we - we were all treated alike so as we wouldn't do it
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well, fortunately mother never went to school so she wasn't capable of - helping us with our school -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She never went to school when she was a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she ask you what you did at school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, she used to ask us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she ever visit the school to meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I think once she did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I - I never saw it. No, I never saw it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Friends there were you know, in little clusters, yes. More so I think with the boys than the girls. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. Not unless their musses - mothers wishes them - wished them to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Would you have stayed longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, I think so. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you attend any part time education like evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I always had too much work to do at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Have you got any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No I don't think so because - after I left I tried to pick up after what I'd missed you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 While you were at work did you have any part time jobs or any means or earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, I had to work all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Tell me about the first one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well the first one was service -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh before I left school I took milk out. Yes. Six o'clock in the morning. Yes. From a quarter to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well they used to put envelopes in the dairy windows you know - on the shops you see. Little order boys - paper boys and - I got this job, milk, I used to get one and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What were the hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well six 'til eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. All round Canning Street and Hoskinson Street and Parliament Street. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 All those steps - every house had steps didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you do it - it wasn't in bottles then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No, it was cans, those - metal cans and you had a big can and then you had a lot of little cans hooked on all round and a measure. Well when you finished you had to go and wash all those - yes. The dairy was at the corner of Hoskinson Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was that Saturday and Sunday as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh all - every morning. Yes, and Sunday. Sunday was the cream morning - when the people had cream you know, little tiny cans like that. Yes. Yes, yes. Oh and they - they used to have a - a round mu
g thing with a big cow on with the milk in - in - in the dairy and a cloth to put over the top, yes. And buttermilk - you could buy buttermilk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And there w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 as dairies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  all over the place wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They'd keep about half a dozen cows wouldn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. Batties in Smithdown Road you know, they - theirs was a big dairy, and Tofflers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 But you would fin in Dove Street, you'd find one in Wye Street round there wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Sumpters at the - in Solway Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 There used to be coal places too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh coal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
yards. Swinburns. Oh, I used to go there for a quarter of coal - a quarter - it was only ninepence a hundredweight. And I used to say, can I have the bogey Mr Swinbank - and he was a big - retired - police - off - superintend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10645980\charrsid4015401 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
nt - yes, and - he'd say, now bring it back, Chestnut. I used to have long chestnut hair you know and I'd say, all right. And there'd be about four girls round the corner waiting and after I'd run this quarter of coal home you know we'd
 all have a little ride round the block in this bogey you know, and then I used; to say, don't come with me when I take it back. Oh dear.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was that the only job you had before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. Well I used to go to this fruit merchant, Banner Gywreth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes. Oh yes. No, two evenings week when the maid was off, yes, to clear the - to clean the table and - and wash up. Yes. I can remember I used to have to put me two plaits all round, it was all - mother used to do it with hairpins and so it in basket plai
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3166427\charrsid4015401 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 s and a white apron on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did they live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They lived in Croxworth Grove, Lodge Lane. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Now how much did you get for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh mother used to get that on her wages when she went. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The one and six a week you got from the milk, did you think it was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - then we did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Give it all to her. I had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was it spent on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I suppose it went in food you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you get on with the other people you worked with - the boss - were they decent people - how did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You mean the dairy? Well it was an elderly lady. It was mother and son run
 the business you see and - she was rather a nice woman, she suffered with - arthritis in her hands and - I liked her very much. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you like the work - did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh taking the milk out - that time it was a job and that's all tha
t mattered. We - we didn't think about what we had to do then we just - plunged into it somehow you know. Head first. Now they're asking - they give the boss an interview now don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the job alter your attitude to work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. I just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Attitude to school I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was your first full time job after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well that was service. For three and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you get it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I went to this place where mother -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Through your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you have to do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well, it was mostly washing up and weeing - waiting on the cook you know and - doing the kitchen. It wasn't a very important job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What hours did you work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we worked from we got up 'til we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You lived in did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. You were on call all the time. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Sundays and Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well you got a Sunday off I think once a month - all day and then you go to a half day a week, it was half days then you kn
ow, you didn't get any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How many servants were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Two - besides me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What were their titles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 One was cook and the other one was house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6955341\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6955341\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 maid. And I was just the - the little - nonentity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did you sleep and eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they had a lovely big bedroom with single beds.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You had three in one bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And the servants ate in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was there a servants hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, the kitchen was like a servants hall - it was furnished and - had easy chairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was there anywhere you could sit when you were not working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well only your bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the mistress supervise all the housework personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, she left it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She passed the orders to the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you feel at ease with the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And the members of the family too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did the servants and the members of the family address each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - Madam I think it was for Miss - the mi
stress. And it would be Sir for the - but I didn't have any connection at all - I was too young you know, but they did. And - the children, one would be - master Stanley or - and the girl would be - Mistress somebody, you know, whatever her name was - her
 first name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you feel that any of them were interested in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, the mistress when she came down to give her orders would - have a little word with all of us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the mistress give any moral guidance to her servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. She would - if she was having visitors she'd tell cook - how a certain people liked a thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were the servants allowed any time to do just what they liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, when the mistress was away they - they used to have a nice easy time of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When could they go out of the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they had their time off you know, unless - if they wanted special and then they used to ask the mistress for it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she mind what they did then - when they returned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well no, I don't think so, no. I never heard complaints.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you feel homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well I didn't really because mother used to come, you see - I don't know what day it was - it was a day that she didn't go to Eleanor and she would go into the basement to wash you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She used to do all the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you lonely or did you have enough companionship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we weren't lonely. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was there anything you particularly liked or disliked about the situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, co
ok was aw - terrible - the cook was worse than the mistress. Oh, she was terribly strict. Sometimes I'd say to her, how much of that do you put in cook, I wanted to learn how to make a special thing, she'd just rap me fingers and tell me to mind me own bu
siness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did the housework go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well the house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6955341\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6955341\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
maid did upstairs. And cook and me was responsible for down below you see. And then we used to have a - a gardener come and he did odd jobs. And then a woman used to come - half a day on a 
Friday to do the front and all that sort of thing. So - we didn't have any dirty work to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your mother came and did the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who made or mended the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Our clothes or the mistress's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The family's clothes - the mistress's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh well she used to save}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6955341\charrsid4015401  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 it and then get it - a woman - a sewing woman in, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh well, she would pay for that I suppose - it was their own house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was there a nanny or servant responsible for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well not when I went, I believe they had a nanny when they were younger. But they were getting on, the children, when I went you see. They were school age - they were getting ready to go to boarding school..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did the adults eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
