\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, but I couldn't tell you what day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. We didn't think of a holiday - because of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What were your wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Sixteen shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you feel that was a fair wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, with food I got, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And the other wages was only three and six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we always gave our money to mother and she gave us back what she thought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You went back to live at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The money was spent on the house wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh nice - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - Miss Peck was a bit irritable you know, but she'd a lot to ru - responsibility, you know, making profits and things like that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you like there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I liked her all right but - I didn't like her when she was bad tempered. I used to keep away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you feel about the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I liked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Did the mistress at the first place you worked give her servants any moral guidance? Such as advising you to go to church or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we always went to church on a Sunday morning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When you were in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh she give them time off to go to church. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were you allowed any time to do just what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, after a certain time in the day. Well - I mean to say, after you served lunch and washed up well - you'd t
wo hours you see, you could do what you liked. And then you started getting ready for dinner at night. Well after dinner was served and you washed up your evenings was your own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you cold go out then if you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she know where you sent to - did she ask?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, she never asked - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Can you remember - were you ever with that family on a Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. These particular people always went away for Christmas. So we - we went home. I went home anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any musical instruments in their home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they have any players?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They used to play - they used to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did anyone in the family sing do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Not that I know of, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they ever make music together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they used to have visitors you know and have a musical evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the parents play any games with their children? You wouldn't know because the children were grown up weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, they were grown up then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, they had a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1036\langfe1033\langnp1036\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1036\langfe1033\langnp1036\insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1036\langfe1033\langnp1036\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1036\langfe1033\langnp1036\insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1036\langfe1033\langnp1036\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
The children had their own library in the room, a bookshelf you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they ever read to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - no, I think they were old enough to - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you remember a funeral in that family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You didn't ever take the children out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever go out with the Master and Mistress on a weekend or Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No, I thin
k he was out at the market and that that much that he used to - they used to have one of those open landaus you know and they used to go drives and that. Yes. Yes. Oh I can see it now driving up the - you know when the Queen goes on her tours in the open 
- well just like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You were telling me all about the landau - do you remember it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you go with the Master and Mistress when they went on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. They went to relatives you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the master or mistress think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I don't know what they thought but we never did it. No. Everything was very quiet - and select.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How often did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they went in the mornings - all four of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That's the father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And the two children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the children go to church or Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, not those children. They just went to morning service and - one of the big churches, I just forget now - round Princes Road somewhere.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did any of the servants attend the same church as the master and mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. And the R.C's could go to their church - we all got our time off. We arranged it between us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If the servants went to the same church as the master and mistress did they all sit together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - they - were give - big contributors to the church and they sat in a pew - their own pew. But - if we wanted to go in that pew we could. But - you see, they didn't leave the house empty, they w
ent to - church and - the same time as they'd go perhaps somebody that was R.C. - if there was anybody there - they would go and then we would go the same time as the mistress at eleven o'clock, but you see the Catholics had the choice of going from eight
 o'clock - yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was grace said at meals by the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we used to say it in the kitchen but I don't know about the master and mistress 'cos we never sat with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the master and mistress take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they never said if they did. They never discussed it with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the master take part in sport, go to the races, play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well he went to races and I think he went - is it canoeing or whatever you call it, you know. You see, he came - he was -
 what origin now, Bannagwyrath - I forget. Yes. He'd be from abroad somewhere and he used to go at these particular times, if he had a holiday but the was a very hard working man, oh yes, mornings out and - you know, supervising his - he was a wholesale f
ruiterer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did he go to a club at all do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - I think if he did go he'd be - go as a guest you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You wouldn't know how - often he went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the mistress go out on her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Very seldom. No. She entertained - afternoon teas and all that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she have any interests outside the home? Did she work for any charities or sit on any committees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She used to do a lot of embroidery - the mistress as I know here, she had a deformity in the fa
ce - a skin deformity and she didn't go into public much but she did a lot of - needlework and artwork for - to give to these charities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she always have this deformity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well no, I think it came at periods - was something in the skin you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the master and mistress go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You told me your master was a fruit importer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Fruit importer, yes. Wholesale you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was he ever away from home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well if he was they all went together like. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the master and mistress have any friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, they had a lot, they used to come, they used to entertain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you see their friends - when did they see their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I - I - I knew they came and I might see them coming in but - they - what did they call them, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 maid, she used to - receive the friends you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they come to dine or did they go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no, what they had if they had food it was at home. Cook always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they ever go to a ball or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, they went to balls. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What kind of people were their friends and callers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they were just the ordinary like themselves, they weren't what you call - snobby well-to-do people you know, they 
were - after all they used to say that - they had to - run the business for their living, they were working - well-to-do people if you understand. They weren't these people that dictated to everybody you know. No. No, they were nice - they were very nice 
people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were the visitors the same class as the master and mistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they'd all be business people you see I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What class would you say that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I'd say it was the middle class - well-to-do, you know, independent. Indep
endent middle class because you couldn't call them - autocrats because they weren't snobby enough for that. You see, they were too - too understanding you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was the mistress the same class as the master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, she was very nice, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the master and mistress treat some of their friends differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No, I don't think so, I never saw it - I never - no. She - when she was giving cook her orders she used to say - Mr so and so and so and so likes - rather likes such a thin
g for - on his meal, you know, on the menu and - if - it was a particular friends she would know what they liked and she would give cook the eye eye. But - she - yes, but she didn't - definitely say if it was impossible, you must get it you know. She was 
that sort of mistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Rather considerate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was the attitude of guests towards the servants - do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they never saw us very much you see, only the house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 maid - she would receive them and get their c
lothes ready like you know when they were going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you think that the master and mistress were content with their station in life or do you think they would have like a higher position?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I don't think they did. I think the worry with them w
as the upbringing of their two children, their son and girl you know and - the mistress and her health. Yes, I think - I think that was their main concern. He used to worry very much about her when she was - ill with her complaint. I never found out what 
it was. Well of course I was young you know, the others were all older than me and if they'd talk they wouldn't let me hear you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your period in service would be between the ages of fourteen and sixteen wouldn't it
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 About - going on that, yes, yes. But those days you were older than you are now you know. I - I mean to say -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 More responsibility?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You had to hold onto your job didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 More so in your case because you had no father did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. Oh we had to work - and work hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Had you known people like your master and mistress before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well only casuals you know - meeting them when I was taking the milk out - when I first started, when I was going to school. I used to know a
 lot of nice people and they were awfully nice but there was one thing they stressed and I think it - I obeyed it you see - that you must go to the side entrance when you delivered anything. And I used to take this milk and cream you know and I always did
 and always closed the gates and everything. But - there was method in the madness you know, I used to get something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Especially Christmastime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you think of them and their way of life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I rather liked them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did their manners and general behaviour seem different from the people you had associated with before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well you knew they were a little bit better off than you were, you know, you mean to say, you did look up and think - oh this is somebody - better than I am. You got that feeling but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What made you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well because I - in one case they'd more money, they could buy the things we couldn't buy, you see. And - it made you think that - they - everybody was a real lady if we could - if she could get what she wanted with the money wasn't she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any other jobs before you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No, I went to work after I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You left that job at about sixteen didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
 at nineteen you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What jobs did you have before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
I'm just trying to think now. After I left service. No, I don't think I did, I went dailies to different places. Mother got a very bad ulcer in her leg and - this is how it started. Sometimes she couldn't
 go to work and I used to have to drop into her place. Washing and char work you know, that sort of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you were more or less a freelance until you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Doing odd jobs for people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How many jobs have you had since the first world war? That's going to set you back a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No it isn't. Well I worked in Threlfaslls in their - in the Royal Water Loaf. I opened that place for them. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Manageress were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 At the bars - not at the gate or anything. But first of all - it's rather a funny thing, soon after was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  my husband - the war - 1914 was started you see and - of course it was only - the allowance - the war allowance was seventeen and six. Well I had six -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Seventeen and six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How many was that supposed to keep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - it was me and one baby. And then - I had six shillings rent and seven and six hire purchase so I couldn't manage. And - I had a word with mother and she said, well I'll h
ave to come up she said, and mind the baby for you. And - it - look for a job. Well, so I said, I've no idea what to do. She said, well go back to what you was she said, the licen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 e catering - like early on, Miss Pecks little place you know, where I was - 
yes, at Miss Pecks little place. So what I did - I went down to Threlfalls - all the way from Bootle to Threlfalls in Truman Street and I had an interview there with Mr Brook was the head walking manager and - two or three other chaps were sitting at a ta
b
le and he asked me all these - lot of questions you know and then he said to me, have you any children? So I said, yes. So he said, the best thing you can do is go home and mind them. So I said, I'm sorry sir but that doesn't feed them. And I - I'd walked
 
you see, got up and thanked them for the interview and came home and I told me mother. So - in the meantime mother had told a friend that lived near to what had happened. So he was passing one night and - his name was Mr Hughes and he was in one of the Pl
a
ce - houses in Derby Road - a rough quarter. So he said to me, I believe you didn't get on very well at the interview. So I said, no, I said, it was terrible. I said, like - I said, he's like a big yard dog that man. So - he said, yes he is, but he's on h
i
s holidays - have another bash. So I went down and - I saw Mr Corley. And it was a house I can remember the corner of Celia Street in Stanley Road and - he said to me, now I want you to start right away. And I started dithering inside you know. So after a
ll the other - men had gone, I suppose they were bo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
ses of a sort, I said to him, listen Mr Corley I have a confession to make. I said, you know I was down here a fortnight ago with an interview with Mr Brooks and I said, of course, I said, when he knew I h
ad a child, I said, he told me to go home and mind me children. So he laughed and said, well never mind, never mind, he said, you go there, he said, and - take this note, he said, to Mr Whitland, and he said, start. Well I started and I got on famous with
 
them. I was no time before I was the - you know, the blue eye, and - he called me on one side one night and I thought I'd done something wrong and he said to me, I thought you said this was your first - job, he said, in public house? I said, yes it is. I 
s
aid, I've been a waitress, I said, in a licensed place but, I said, nothing like this drawing pints of beer and things like that. He said, well you're shaping very well. So I said, well you see, I was born in the business, perhaps that has something to do
 
with it. Oh, he said, that has a lot to do with it. So he said, well I've to tell you now, he said, you've got to go to the Queens Hotel, Moseley Road. So I said, oh I didn't want to leave here. He said, no, but they think it'll be nearer home with you ha
v
ing - some - kiddie you see. So I went to this house and I was in - well in there too. But the only thing was - all the staff had to wash floors - so much floors and - I don't know whether it was me that couldn't stand up, that was weak to it or not but y
o
u know I felt it a bit hard. Well the same thing happened there. The - called on one side one night and he said, I was wanted and - like to see me and then they said that I was picked for the Royal Water Loaf. And I opened it. I was there six weeks, I nev
er did a hands turn and they just - walked round in a black dress and supervised. Did the cellar work and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was the wages like in those jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well when I started the first one in Stanley Road it was sixteen shillings a week and I h
ad bus fares to pay out of it but sometimes the people would say, will you have a drink - you have a drink. Well - it - I was a bit nervous there so I said to the boss, I said, now I don't drink but these people ask me to have a drink but I said, God know
s I could do with the money. He said, you see this little glass? And I said, yes, I do. So he said, well put your money in there he said, and tell them you'll have the drink later on. So - and I made no end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What were your wages finally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - T
hrelfalls were very good - you only got eighteen shillings but you got a bonus twice a years. And that bonus was paid out in the number of years that you were there you see, so I think the first I got was fifteen - ten to fifteen pound, I wouldn't put a s
tated price but, between that and then it went more and more and more. And of course when I went into the Waterloo Hotel they didn't serve outside people - it was just residen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ials and members. That was very select. All the big noises of Threlfalls used to come - Mr Tonge and all those people. And - I got two pounds ten there. Well I thought - I was on the same fo}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
ting as the mistress you see. And then of course - the tips was much - bigger you see. So - I started to save a little bit you know. Oh yes. That was a good job I didn't because I needed it later on, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Have you had any other jobs since then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh only the railway. Yes. You see, when I got - when the husband came home I started with another baby you see. Of course things like that put you off you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And then you worked in the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - three months after he - first of all I worked in the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market Hotel, I told you didn't I. You see. And - that got bombed. So from that I went into the railways.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you go straight into the canteen on the railways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And you stayed there until now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes, I had some letters here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 From Charlie Gallagher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no. Charlie Gallagher was the union man. He came to me when I first starte
d there and he said, what about joining our union? I said, not on your nellie. I said I know darned well your union can't do anything for caterers and, I said, you'd only just be taking my money for nothing. And I said, I want it in my pocket, not in your
s. He laughed like anything. He said, you're a bit - fly aren't you? And I said, yes, you are too. But we - we got on all right, Charlie and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In all your working life would you have preferred another kind of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No I don't think so. I loved m
e job you see. You see, at school I was very interested and passed with full honours at domestic science. The cooking and all that sort of thing attracted me. No, I don't think I would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you serve an apprenticeship - I suppose you just picked it up didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well I started at the bottom you see. You see when I - yes - when I went to - what do you call it - Chapel Street, to Miss Peck - I started in the kitchens watching them doing and then - when you're in service you watch cooks. I used to 
get rapped on the fingers for asking questions. Yes. I was interested you see, all the time, in that sort of work - so, I didn't - I didn't worry about having to - to do it. The only thing is, I wanted to climb higher all the time. I'll tell you what I li
ked - even in the public houses. If it was a run down place I loved to pioneer 'em - pull the takings up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your dad did that originally didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. I did that in - Edghill anyway. The - oh the agent said, we never knew it was humanly poss
ible for you to do what you've done. He said, I wish we'd had you when this place first opened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Actually it collapsed didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It was dreadful. It was dreadful. And then I went from there - to Park Lane to pick that one up. The - one of the he
ads in the railway catering said, if Mrs Thompson can't pick this place round in a month nobody can.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was the railway canteens themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. So I - I went to Park Lane and I was there I think for two or three years and worked that up and
 trained a cook to take over but - she didn't - it wasn't in her you see. You see, always they thought they had to do was - whatever anybody asked them for that side was pass it over. Well you see, you can't run a place on losses. You've got to make wages
 and everything haven't you. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you enjoyed your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh yes, I have - I've loved - I've loved every bit of it. I was just looking if I could find those letters for you. And - I was left you know. I - I told them in Edghill I was - I'd had 
enough and I was left and - one agent, but there's loads of these, do you know, if I was a young woman I could get a job anywhere. I was looking for the letter where they sent me -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That's only 1965 - it's not so long ago?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I worked 'til I was seventy-two, I told you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I thought the railways chucked you out when you were sixty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - they were glad to get me back in. It didn't apply - it didn't apply for catering - the canteen. We're separate you see, yes. Oh if we'd worked for 
the railway we'd have got - a big wage. But we didn't, we come under the catering. Anyway perhaps when I see you again I'll find these letters. But - they were they very - nice, you know, I can meet any of me bosses in the street and speak to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It's n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
ce to be able to say that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It is. I never had any - trouble with them. But staff - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The only problems you do get are staff problems you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, that's right. Yes. And - when I went back after Park Lane and they said they wanted
 me back at Edhill, I said to the boss when I went back - the secretary Mr Morris, now listen - this place is run wild and it's gone very bad and if I've got to put in in order you've got to back me up with it. And not coming if you don't. And he did. Yes
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you have enjoyed your working life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It's very nice to hear that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you belong to any trade union at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well the employers had the interest but they never could - they - employer but - they never could get the employees to - put it into practice. It was too difficult - they couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you think there was divisions of interest amongst the workers themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes, if you got one good one the bad ones'd soon - convert them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Some people say in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, did you you 
think this was correct or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - there was if he was a - a real trained craftsmen, where he'd served seven years or five years to a trade. And then another a man come in and wanted - got the same money - he couldn't do the work, he had to rely o
n him for the difficulties well he - it rubbed his back up you see. It would you wouldn't it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Would you say that full time work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Full time? No, if you took a job on full time you took it on and you did it, it never altered me at all you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did starting full time work change your relationship you're your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 With your brothers or sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well the brothers was always away at sea you know. They weren't at home very much and as I told you, the eldest sister was - in service. She wasn't at home very much - there was only the younger sister and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No. We went to Sunday school. We went to church three times on Sunday. We were - we had to go. Three nights a week Band of Hope when we were going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You told me earlier how you spent your spare time - how did you spend your spare time after you left school? Did you go cycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, mother always had a - she used to do a lot of washing you know, I told you - Frisby Dykes. Well I either had to do so much }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 roning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Even after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 More or less until you got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have much spare time at all - for the first couple of years you were working for the Bannerthwaites weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Bannagwareths. Bannagwareths. He used to be in - Clayton Square you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you wouldn't get much spare time there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He was with - in like Waterworth's you know - you see, only I think his was more the continental fruit, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever go out cycling, dancing, picnics, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No - sometimes we'd go to Sefton Park - and have our tea there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No, didn't go out much even when I was courting. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you make many new friends after you left school - boys or girls?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, no new ones. I - I still have some old ones that I meet you know, that I went to school with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you bring your friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, we did but - there was no home life as regards bringing them home for tea or anything like that - we couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, we were all the neighbours, you know, all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, she knew them all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh I'll say. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Ten minutes late and - and she was behind the door and give you nice little rap as you stepped in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What time - did she have time for various ages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - I remember the first dance I went to she said I had to be home at ten o'clock - it was a military affair. Oh what did they call them - Red Jack Militias. Yes. At George's Hall and I had to wait 'til I went out
 before I could put a bit of powder on. And had to be home at ten o'clock anyway. I think a lot of us got a - hired a cab. Yes, and we came home in this cab. We didn't pay of course - the chappies paid and - oh when she saw me getting out of a cab, I thou
ght I'd never live 'til the next morning. Ooh you - no more cuts for you - no more dances. I'll dance you. Get up those stairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What age were you when you were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Nineteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How long had you known your husband then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 About eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well I think I told you before. My brothers were on the Alexander Touring Company boats. And - he was - on these tug boats and one brother left and went away to sea. And in the meantime we'd moved and there was no
 way of letting him know so mother - sent me - with a friend - oh I forget - I think it was Langton Dock and you could get on the overhead and you got right off and the - I think the name of the boat was the Fesselie or the - Fessa something anyway and - 
I
 waited for this boat to dock and he - his tug was docking it you see. So he seen the two of us standing there and after they'd docked the boat and they'd tied the tug up he came up and he asked - if we were waiting for anyone. So I said, yes, I'm waiting
 
for me brother, I think he's on this ship. And told him the story that we'd moved and I wanted to - take him home. It was only a couple of streets away but mother didn't want him walking round. Those days they had a big sailors bag you know, big long canv
a
s bag. And - then when he came - of course they knew each other you see, the two - me brother and he knew each other because my brother had worked in - on these tugs and - my brother was on the Sandon I think it was the tugboat and it turned over and I th
ink that put him off you see and he - managed to get saved and - then the brother invited him up to the house and that was how I knew him you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did he come from? Was he a Liverpool lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, he was a - his father - was coal heaver and used to import all the men from - Ireland over you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Quite a number of people - they used to live down - Scotland Foad way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Athel Street. Yes. But when I met him he'd left Athel Street and they lived in - Bootle. Off in Rose Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you save up money before getting }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well, no, I think his father }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  him a bit you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother help you in setting up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well that was the rift you see - he was a different religion and my mother was against it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was he a Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How long were you engaged?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh there was - we just said we'd get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  you know, there was no - yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 My father was a Catholic and my mother was a Protestant but it made no difference to our family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh it didn't to me. It didn't to me, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you turn for him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No, nobody turned. No. No. When the priest came he said that he was a Catholic and I said I didn't want him to be anything else. And - then he said about me turning and my husband said, no, she - I don't wish her to, he said, until - you kno}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid32720\charrsid4015401 w, he - he said, she wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 nts to and he said, don't press. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you describe the wedding? Where did it take place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh, a registry office of course you see.
 Yes. Yes. We came home and - of course I wasn't twenty-one you see so mother had to - sign papers. And - the chappie in Brough - High Park Street Registry Office was my sister's - boss you see. She was in service with them and - he was very upset about i
t you know but - of course - there you are, and then I went home, we'd got a flat in Bootle - very nice - very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have a party at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you get many presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, nothing. Nothing at all. No. His father gave me tw
o gold sovereigns when the first baby was born. She was born - just almost two years after we were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No. No. We were glad to have our flat with the bit of furniture.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 A flat in Bootle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh we were with - with the old lady for about two years. And - of course I - just before the baby was born I didn't want the baby born there you see and - we got a four roomed house off a chappie - he lives in - opposite the No
rth Park, Bootle - Flannagans, yes. We got a four roomed house in - Aikenside Street, off Summerside -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where the floods always used to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They've altered that now you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh a lovely little house - I wish I had it now. Yes. I'd give two of these up for that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How long were you there - were you there 'til the and of 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we were there a long time. I was there about eight years in that house. The second baby was born there. The one that's in America now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Six shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was a lot wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The average rent was about four and a tanner wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did those houses have bathrooms at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. Little four roomed kitchen houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You've heard of Klondike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well some of them used to have bathrooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well perhaps they put it in you see. No, we had a nice little glass conservatory outside you know in the yard. But the 1914 war started while we lived there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How old was your husband when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well he was seven years older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So he would be twenty-six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was your husband's job when you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Tugboats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He was a tugboat captain?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, mate at that time but he - he could take captain's - he did take over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That would be a good job wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Two pound five a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Which was good money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. But you had to keep two houses. You had to p
ack his basket for his food and - and he took it on the ship and - and then I had to live at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Would he be away any length of time - he might be mightn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh, sometimes two or three days, it just depended if they had to wait in the river for any ship you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And sometimes they had to go and stay on the continent for a ship didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did he have any other jobs before or after he did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well after - they - somebody met him while he was on these tugboats
 and said that they'd offer him a job in the White Star Line. As a rigger. So he used to go out at two in the morning and rig the - he was a good climber you see. And he used to rig these ships for the - dockers for to get the cargo off you know. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was more of a shore job wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He'd be home every night wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes. And he - he - no, sometimes he was out all night, yes. And - he got very good wages then, but you see he wasn't very long in it before the war came. H
e needn't have gone but he did go, he said he - he couldn't stand the - men all talking about their boys going and that so - of course he went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He'd be about thirty at the time wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What jobs did he have after he left the Army?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well he didn't have any - he never worked you see. When he came out of the Army he was up in Winniker for ages - he was gassed you see and he'd bad health. Well before that he said to me, I'll go into the - the discharged him, he said, I'll go into 
the Navy - the eaglet he said, and get in the Navy. Perhaps it' - ll do me good, he said, me lungs. So he passed all right and went into the - on the H.M.S. Cyclops - one of the little boats taking the stuff out and the letters and that to them and - of c
ourse the war finished and when he came home this gas business you see, started, yes. And he never worked after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He was pensioned was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No, we never got anything. No. I had - I worked - I kept him for four years before he died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When did he die then - what year would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh don't ask me that now. I was only out at Ford the other week. Easter. yes. I could look it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you work while your husband was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes. When he went in the Army I had to earn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did he feel about you working when he was in the Army?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well I - everybody did it so I didn't notice it you see. I'll tell you what I used to do, because you see I was pregnant when he went away, so I used to rush - get the baby and rush down to the La
bour Exchange in Primrose Road - in - no, bottom of Moseley Road, and - get a green card and we went aboard the ships - cleaning and - yes - but - they used to spot me you know - of course I suppose you could - it's a thing you can't hide and - they used 
to give me nice light job. Put -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was before the baby was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes, putting the state curtains up or cleaning brasses and - the - the women all used to come in the dining room for their dinner. Oh my God, it used to make me sick. They'd had 
big tins you know and the women'd be eating the meat like a lot of wild animals. And - they'd find me sitting in - in a little tiny room, you know, on a stool and - the cook or the chef'd say, have you had your dinner? And I'd say, oh no, I couldn't eat w
i
th - I couldn't eat with that gang. And they'd find me something - a little bit of something. I'd say - ooh, I've got a sandwich. And they - they'd put liquid milk - you know, tinned milk in their tea. Well I couldn't drink that. Oh, mind you I was funny.
 I know I was. But I couldn't help what I'd had you see. It had stuck to me and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did your husband feel about you going to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh terrible. Terrible. Oh I had to give it up. And when he came down - he was home on leave and he came down look
ing for me. I'd had a straw bed and was going up the gangway. A straw bed over me - shoulder you know. You had to take it they said, so many women on this you know, they had to go you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You were saying about taking the straw beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7409488\charrsid4015401 Up the - on the Maurita}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
nia and the Old Olympic - do you remember - the soldiers - the troops. You - you know all down below and there was great big gullies in the ships and one day I saw a rat run along and you know the way I was - oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did your husband like his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh the tugboats and the - White Star. Oh he loved it. Yes, he loved the White Star because there was danger in it. He was mad. No, he was very well educated really, he was - a bit above - me in education because he went to Efferveths College
. He went to the college and was a Jesuit and - and - he told me - he told his father that - he couldn't carry on the priesthood you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He didn't go to Stowyhurst or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh he wanted to - his father wanted him to be a priest. You see, his mother died at his birth, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You had children didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I had four. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What were the dates of births before 1918 - how many did you have before 1918 - you just had one didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I'd have two wouldn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Do you know what year they were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - Winnie was born on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7409488\charrsid4015401 twelfth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  of September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Now don't ask me that - Mary was born the first one - two years after I was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You must have been about twenty-one when she was born then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Just on twenty-one. Yes. Just a couple of months before I was twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were your children born at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh all at home. We used to put one and six away a week for the midwife. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any medical help then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Only for one - the dead born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No. Mother used to tell us the quieter we were the - the better for us. Not to make a fuss. And she worried and - I said, well if you can have thirteen I can have one. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you get on about your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I did what she said - I kept quiet. But - apart from a little moan of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your husband help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, not at the birth. Oh no. He waited for the nurse to go down and tell him what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How soon were you out of bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - about ten days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you come out of bed for the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh well it just depended you know how you were - what sort of a - confinement you'd had you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you manage about the house while you were in bed - did somebody come and help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh mother did - yes - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she do everything for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And then - oh yes, she did all the washing and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Saw to your gruel. A midwife, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 But you didn't have a nurse for the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you feed your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you enjoy feeding the child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. For nine months, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any difficulties in feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You mean in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In feeding and looking after the child generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No, only - a few months like after she was born I had to get back to work of course and - I noticed, you know, I used to have a bit of pain like - over excess milk and that. Yes. Oh terrible pain.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If you needed advice who did you ask - did you ask your mother - if you needed advice about looking after the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I didn't panic, it was funny. No, I didn't panic at all. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you need advice then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, not until she was - she'd be about three or four you know and I took her to the doctor, she'd chicken pox or something you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If the baby was asleep would you wake it for a feed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. I never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If it cried before normal time would you feed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, becaus
e in those days there was none of this every two hours and every four hours - we knew when it was crying it was hungry and wanted changing - so we fed it and changed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you do if it didn't seem hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I never had that experience. Nine were little wolves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How long would you let it go on feeding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well 'til it was satisfied, it knew when it had had enough you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When did you first give it solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well about - six months. If I made gruel I'd give it a - a 
couple of teaspoonfuls you know, so much. And if not I used to get a - a - arrow root biscuit and give it half crushed with a drop of hot water and butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you gradually wean the baby or suddenly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh gradually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the baby mind at all do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well sometimes it used to - nose about you know and want its food but - you - were weaning it of course and - there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you think at any time that it did any harm to the baby to let it cry or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No, we never - 
if it had been fed and was clean and all that sort of thing we knew it was - if it was crying and it was at the teething age we'd pet it a little bit, I used to, and comfort it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you punish it when it was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How much did your husband have to do with the children when they were babies under one year? He was in the Army wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. I never had much help with the kiddies, only from mother you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He didn't feed them or change their nappies or get them to sleep or play with them did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, he wasn't there - most of the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you know what your husband earned?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How much of that did he give to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - almost all of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you discuss with your husband how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well, yes, if - I never went into debt unless I said to him well, should we so and so and - he'd say well I think we can manage it because such a thing's finished and that could be so much money towards it. We never plunged into a lo
t of debt. We sort of got - the necessities thing, if we hadn't all the money well we would get it on here purchase but we wouldn't get that and have a lot more as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Finish one before you started another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And there were four rooms in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Two down and two up. Yes. Aikenside, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I did it at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were the clothes made or mended by you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they were mended but I didn't make them. You can't - when - you want a sewing matching and all that sort of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And you had to go to work too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were the clothes bought new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7409488\charrsid4015401  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh new mostly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did you buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we used to get a clothing cheque and buy them on that. Stirlers was the name one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Everybody went to Stirlers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was the name of the other firm - Elsies was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, Elsies - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And the same with the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you always but the shoes new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 On the cheque?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your husband help with jobs in the house - did he do any cleaning, cooking, washing, washing up, fires, decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh yes, he'd do anything - if you shut the doors and didn't let anybody in to see him doing it. And you were having a having and you'd be near the end he'd do anything and - if - mother wasn't there and you were confined in bed he'd lay a nice tray up an
d bring it up as good as any woman. Yes, he watched what I did and he used to do the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did he help with the children - like dressing and undressing them - bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, if you were - weren't well he' would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Read aloud to them - tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did he ever take them out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Not very far but he would take them out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did he look after the children while you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well no, he couldn't because, you see, I had mother there - he was away most of their life you see. There wasn't a long }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  life. I - yes - and he was in the Army a lot you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And he died when he was thirty-five didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And - yes - and then - he was ill for so long that I never bothered him much to d
o anything. Took him all his time to walk about. So you see, I - I had mother you know, she - only for her I couldn't have gone to work or anything. I don't know what would have happened to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did your mother live in the house with you or did she come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, she lived - didn't live far - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any regular household tasks for the children to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well when they - after the father died like and they were going to school I moved up here you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Up to Waver Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. And then - mother lived in Wavertree you see. And - they used to - wash up and do a little bit, but not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they have regular jobs - like polishing the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What time did your children go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh they used to go early, my children, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, they used to go themselves - I wasn't there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the children share a bed or a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 They had two single beds in the one bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And you and your husband slept in the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well he wasn't there then - you see, he'd gone. By the time they - he never saw them grow up you know. The youngest child doesn't remember her father - this one in Wales.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The eldest one would only be seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She just barely remembers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 The eldest one would be seven wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, yes. She just barely remembers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That would be Mary wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. Winnie. Yes, the one in America. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Which room did you use for bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 For bathing you mean? Oh the - always the scullery because you were near the gas stove to heat the water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How often did that take place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we always had an annual at the weekend but they used to go to the baths in the week you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When did the children have clean clothes - what day would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they'd have them when they want - when they liked you know - two or three times a week in the summer. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where were the meals eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we had a - the front livin
g room you know. But mostly they went to their grandmother's for their dinner. Because - because it was near the school and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did you cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh in the scullery on the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You had a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Gas stove yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When was breakfast eaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well we - there was only like the two children at the last and me and we used to have breakfast - they used to go to school and I used to get on the bus for work - on the tram. Were no buses then - there was trams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You were all together there weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
When your husband went to work how did he manage for his first meal - did he take it with him or did you make it ready for him the night before or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, there were dock canteens you know. Oh you mean when he was working or when he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When he was working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh well there were dock canteens where he got his food. And then I was at home you see, to do his evening meal. But - when I went to work he'd get his own meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you usually have for breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well, in the winter we always had porridge. And toast or fried bread. That was your breakfast. And - in the summer time we'd just have toast and - jam or something like that you see. They never - we cut the porridge when it come to the summer. Yes. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We always called it dinner time at twelve o'clock - did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Now it's called lunch time - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have anything different on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, we used to get a - a little bit of roast or a - that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And how about evening meals on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we used to have currant cakes and sometimes we'd break away and make a jelly and - things like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you have for breakfast on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh, it was mostly - and - bacon frie
d, you know, piece of - fat bacon. When - in the summer when the eggs were cheap they used to be imported eggs and you got them twenty-four for a shilling. Yes. Oh yes. We used to - go mad and have a little bit of bacon and egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you make bread at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Always made our own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Mm. Mother - mother used to make the bread and send it to the bake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7409488\charrsid4015401 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 house. Yes. No, we never made wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you make medicines at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Only the linseed tea. And sulphur and treacle. Brimstone and treacle. Yes. Yes. Well we used to make that. The - the medicine was a lic - dose of li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7409488\charrsid4015401 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 orice powder. That was - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Terrible stuff wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It used to be the idea of everybody in those days to clear everybody out every week end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh - a real - we didn't want antibiotics then. You had to take that and your mother'd hold your nose while you took it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You didn't have an allotment or a garden did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you wouldn't grow your own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 We bought them, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were they tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no. Fresh. We never had anything tinned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any hens at all or pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, mother had a few hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 She did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh we had a little bit of meat - nearly every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was it tinned or fresh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, fresh meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever go short so your children or your husband could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh yes, we used to - if they could eat more we left our dinner 'til the last. We always served them, you know. And if they could eat more there wouldn't be very much left for us but we had to make do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And your husband did the same - did he have a larger helping than the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No, he was a very small eater. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were the children allowed to talk during the meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were they allowed to choose what they wanted to eat from what was cooked or did they have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no, they had everything. They had the same as we had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What was your attitude to some food left uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I don't remember seeing any. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the children have to wait until things on the table, such as the salt, were offered to them or could they ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh no, they'd help themselves, but - more or less it would all be seasoned and they wouldn't want any extras you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Would they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were they taught to hold their knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, they were taught that and the spoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were they allowed to bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When did members of the family leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well they used to ask permission. Say grace and thank God for a good meal and then leave the table. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did all the members of the family present for the meal sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well there was only like the - us, you see. Yes, I know - and a big family, you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who was the meal served by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh well, I always put it out when I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In what order did you serve it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - the father got served first and then the - the eldest - you know, it come down - the baby was the last always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What method did you have of feeding the children who were too young to sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, they more or less in those days, you know, they watched what the others were doing and they wanted to do 
the same. They wanted to feed themselves before they were able but - when they were babies and we started giving them a little bit of ordinary food - we used to have them in a high chair. With a table at the front and we'd feed them and give them there di
nner and then they'd be banging on this tray in the front while you had yours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How old would they be before they joined the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh they wouldn't be very old. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When your children were young did you feel there was a right and wrong way of bringing them up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about bringing up children or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well the short time I was with him he was agreeable - you know - to the schooling and everything what they wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you talk about this between yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well, he used to say sometimes - I don't mind what school they go to as long as they're educated. He was great on the education you see. And - funny, although he was a Catholic he wouldn't send them to a Catholic school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He was a rather unusual Catholic wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes. Yes. He said - it - it wasn't - that he didn't want them to be brought up Catholics but he - he could see for himself that the children in the - other school got more education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It is true you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 In those days the most time was spent on religious instruction.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes, that's right. But the instruction was very hard at that time in the Catholic religion. And - we sent her to school quite near home and then t
he - the got reports the teachers you see and they sent for her father and - he said, I want my child educated and I brought her here. He took her himself. The first one. He said, and I went her - that was Mary - he said, I went her educated here. Never m
ind what anybody says - her mother and me are both agreed that she comes to this school. The interference stopped then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any trouble with his people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well his father was a bit - you know, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever experience any catholic priests coming round to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Chasing your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, and me. Yes. Yes. Yes, he did - and saying you weren't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401  and all that. They say they don't say it but they do. They do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Actually my father hit one - and he was brought up - he got away with it though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. Yes. Well it was insulting him in his own house wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 My people got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3963911 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
 in a registry Office like you did you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 People outside Liverpool don't realize just how much you suffered and your husband and my father and mother suffered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Yes, oh we did. I used to cry for hours you know, at nights, because all his cousins and that you know when he'd take me to see them, they'd give him a chair and leave me 
standing and he used to get up - sit down and get up and say to me - sit down Flo. Florrie - he wouldn't call me Flo. Yes, sit down. And I - yes - and then I'd say to him, oh let's go home - after when they weren't about you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It wasn't fair because you didn't give a knock at their religion at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 But they were always prepared and anxious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If you brought a child up as we were as Church of England.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes. Well one of his relations said to me once, she sai
d, you know the Catholic religion's the only religion. I said, do you think so? She said, I'm sure it is. And I said, well it isn't you know, because, I said, the rock of St Peter crumbled. I said, and - it will cruble you know if you go on like this. I s
aid, we've all got to live haven't we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 It threw my father right away from religion altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, well it did my - my husband was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Was there anyone you used to talk to if you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, only mother - that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And she was alive when they were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How often did you see her - daily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh every day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ask her advice about bringing up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did she have the same ideas as you had of bringing up the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, sometimes - she used to think I was a bit - strict you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did your mother-in-law think about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No mother-in-law. She died at my husband's birth you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Can you tell me some of the things you felt you ought to do for your children - affection, safety, food discipline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well - no, the only thing is - I felt that - you know with them having no father - that I couldn't do enough for them, you see, I wanted to do more all the time but - of cou
rse they were fortunate children I think now when I come to look at some of the children with fathers. They got a lot more, they got a holiday - I never got one - but they got a holiday every year. Oh yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You were in a job where you could earn the money weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I - I got it in tips - the wages weren't there but - and then you had to keep up appearance you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 About discipline and safety - did you have any ideas about discipline - how you ought to bring your children up -
 that they should obey immediately - did you have any ideas about food or safety in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
I was worried sometimes about the stoves and that but I used to say - sometimes I'd go to work and I'd leave everything for them in the oven you see and I'd
 say, now before you open this oven turn the gas off, you see, Had - I had to train them, it was a big responsibility you know. But - that was after mother died of course you know and they had to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 After you mother died, I see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well really she w
asn't able to look after them - when they got to about ten or eleven she began to - it began to get too much for her you see. So I started to take a little bit away from her you know, aw much as I could. But - I used to say, to them, now don't be gadding 
off to the park unless I say you can go, and all that sort of thing. With them being girls I used to be afraid of them getting into trouble you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Where did you work then then - at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh when they were little I'd be in the Corn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15232514\charrsid4015401 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 market in Liverpool wouldn't I - you know in town. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you want your children to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, I - I wanted them to - I always encouraged them to come and tell me anything that happened. And they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well they were very good really in - sometimes you know, they'd want a thing - to dress a certain way and I used to think it wasn't nice, you know, and I'd say - I'd say, well I don't think that sort of thing'd suit 
you and they'd say - oh mother, but I'd like one you know. And I'd say, well all right, we'll go and we'll see it, you can see yourself in the glass and - and - we always come to some agreement without getting cross with each other you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When your children were young did you and your husband ever manage to leav}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15232514\charrsid4015401 
e them so you could go out tog}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. We - we never got that far you see with - it being a short marriage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you let your children join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did you bring them up to consider most important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well obedience really. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you tell them they should hit back Or nit if another child hurt them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, I never told them that, no. I used to say to them, if any
body said anything nasty to them I used to give them the same teaching as mother gave us - walk away. Just ignore them. Just - ignore them and you'll get in no trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any other children you discouraged them from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, they chose nice friends. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 If your children did something you disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well I'd just tell them that they'd no right to do it and - and I didn't like it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever punish them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 W
ould you say that your children received the ideas they had about how to behave from both parents or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well there was only me you see. There was only me. But - they used to get a lot of ideas - they al
ways seemed to mix with better people, you see, more - people that - you know - they - they'd go to church with and - now Derek Guyler, you know, he's on the - television, well this daughter in America used to go to the same church as his and she used to 
g
o to discussions. She - they met with a nice class of person and they learned from those people you see, that if you mixed with anybody - what we call beneath you you've got to be friendly with them but if you mix with them everyday life you don't learn a
nything from those people. Yes. And - I always encouraged them to do that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You told me your mother looked after your children while you were at work didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 How did you feel about leaving your children with your mother - did you feel quite happy about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, she was good to - better than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Some people think that children should be with their mother all the time - others think that it is not necessary and it does them good to be with other people quite a lot - what do you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
I think that. I - I think that if they mix with - if they're nice people I think it's a good thing for them. I do. And if they've got your good advice and the back of their mind they won't do much wrong. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 When your children had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they receive any presents or have anything different to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, they'd have to have some little presents and they'd have to have a s
ponge cake. We never got any further than a sponge cake. And - we'd stick a couple of candles on - we might put some icing on it you know and put a couple of candles on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did they have a little bit of a party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 But it was nearly always a new dress you know. Or - or a new something like that. Or a new coat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were all your children girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No, there was a boy. No. They - they - couldn't have toys you know. Might have a little tiny thing. Snakes and ladders or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Any present they had had to be of some use?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well somebody else had to buy it - mine was always a new dress or a new coat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Can you remember anything you did with your husband and children on Christmas Day? We're back to square one again because your e
ldest child was only seven when your husband died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Well they wouldn't - died - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And the first couple of years he was in the Army wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 He was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 And then he was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 So you can't remember what happened during Christmas time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we didn't have any turkeys or anything like that I can tell you that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, he played the violin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Husband, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did any of you sing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Oh we used to laugh sometimes, he'd strike up The Wearing of the Green. And I used to - I used to say to him, oh go in the other room and wear that green. And another one - Destiny. And all the classics he liked - oh he loved the classic musi
c. If there was a concert anywhere I used to try, you know, and scrape the money up to get him to go to a musical concert, yes..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did he ever go to St Georges Wall to hear the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh he went everywhere if he - if it was music. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you play any games with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. I - I played all my games at work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You told me sometimes you used to be so tired coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Oh dreadful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were there any books or newspapers or magazines in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. We had a newspaper but I used to just read that. Oh we used to have a - a little book c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15232514\charrsid4015401 alled - ooh it was a little tin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 y thing, now what was it, a very old - book. Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Uncle Tom's Cabin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15232514\charrsid4015401 No. It was a - A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 ldy's magazine. Oh dear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you belong to a library?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you read aloud to each other or to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
No, they used to read to me very often. Yes. When they got older you know. They took after their father for intelligence you know. Oh yes. Well the one in America is a lecturer you know - in the university. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were the children taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No, we never bothered with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Were they taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Who took them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 I took them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the children ever go out with just their father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 What did they do on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well we went over to New Brighton or Sefton Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did the children go away at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes, they went away - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 
Well they - they used to go what they called camp at school you know, and then after that - when they got older, they would book and go away with friends, you know, different places - Isle of Man, Torquay and places like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days and Sundays - you were working - did you work a seven day week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Well Saturdays, more or less of a morning it was - as - the annual baths and - then Saturday afternoon we'd 
go shopping. And - if we had in what we wanted well I'd do extra cleaning you see. Then - Sun - go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 You didn't work on Sundays did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Not - Saturdays, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Or Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 No. Yes. And then on a Sunday morning if it - in the summer thi
s was - we used to get up and go to Heswell - hills for the day, take a picnic. It was the only time I had with them you see. And - if it wasn't too good the weather we'd perhaps only just go to New Brighton or West Kirby, but we went somewhere in the sum
mer every Sunday. To get them out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you or the children have any different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you think it wrong to work or enjoy yourself on a Sunday or did you think it did not matter?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Well - it was a-case of 
having to you see, and of course we were taught in the - the religion that was necessary was - had to be done you see but - not to look for unnecessary work on Sundays, to keep it the Sabbath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Did you attend a church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes, we used to go to Central Hall. Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7628901 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 That was Methodist wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4598894 FT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9765293\charrsid4015401 Yes. Yes.
